description:
Use your newly-acquired genderbending abilities as a 'FlipWitch' to conquer evil monsters, giant bosses, and Monster Girls across the land!
You'll have to use your wits in this quirky adventure to seduce everyone around you!

0.1.10.description:
Nightly release.  There's a few longstanding bugs still.

Bugfixes:
- Fixed issue with Long Distance Relationship not properly triggering
- Fixed an issue where picking up Gobliana's luggage did not set a variable.
- Removed an erroneous wand upgrade.
- Fixed wand upgrades so you don't get multiple in a single send.
- Fix gacha machines possibly erroring on gachapons off.
- Fix Sensei incorrectly never giving you a cutscene if your wand upgrade is too high.
- Fix gachas not using the right order (didn't i do this already?)
- Fix peach upgrades not increasing heal amount
- Fix several logic errors:
  - Slime form wasn't required for the pipe after Goblin Queen
  - Health in Shady Sewers didn't require anything.
  - Fungella locations didn't require the key to the door
  - Slime Citadel didn't require its key
  - Gachas were using index to check when they were in logic, when it should have been index + 1

Tweak:
- Reduced reduction of Protective Barrier from half reduction each to a quarter each.
- Remove item popups for now when you receive an item.
0.1.10.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.1.10

0.1.11.description:
New Features:
- If you receive an important item, the "purchase" sound effect plays.
- If you receive a trap, the "boss crystal fall" sound effect plays.

Bugfixes:
- Fixed issue where on starting a new game, received items were locked unless you restarted.
- Deathlink no longer spams you.
- Disables the item popup for most items sent to the player so you don't get to freely move during the intro.
- Complete received items rework.  Worst case, if you believe you are missing something, dying will fix it.
- Fixed issue where the Cat Statue quest would not send.
- Forces a requirement that you must visit the three spots for Cat Statue and Summon Stones before finishing the quest.
  - This avoids a potential softlock as if you finish beforehand these spots vanish.
- Fix rewards from Beatrix only giving the first pass of items.
0.1.11.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.1.11

0.1.12.description:
New Features:
- Text filtering.
  - If the sent message is a hint or obtained item not relevant to you, it is skipped.
- Text coloring based on players, item flags, etc.

Bugfixes:
- Attempt to fix supposed bug with seeds defaulting to -1 and saving.
- Fix logic for Unlucky Cat Statue and Summoning Stones
0.1.12.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.1.12

0.1.13.description:
Changes:
- Archipelago UI changed
  - Uses a window, similar to how HP2 does it currently.
  - Text window is placed on the bottom instead of the top.
- If the user hits F8, all normal game input is blocked, allowing the player to type freely.
- The last known working connection is saved to a file in the ArchSaves folder, and is pulled from on load, to avoid having to re-type the last game's connection information.
- Most locations correctly collect (chests, gacha coins, health/mana container pickups.
  - Anything else is NOT CHANGED.  Includes Shops, Gacha machine pulls, etc.
  - Shops may be included later.

Bugfixes:
- Remove popup that occurs during the Goblin Queen victory regarding the item that is normally the crystal being removed, as it allowed the player to move during a cutscene.
- Fix generation including one of every filler item before running the actual filler method, which caused a rogue "Nothing" to be added to the pool.
- Removed local handling of received items
  - This is done in an attempt to fix the issue where some items aren't sent.  Not confirmed but theorized its a chase condition regarding indexes.  We'll see if it fixes it.
0.1.13.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.1.13

0.2.0.description:
Full release of Flipwitch.  Perhaps its still buggy, but its in a good place, I think.

Changes from pre9:
- Added logic for peach charges and health upgrades.

Bugfixes from pre9:
- Fixed logic issue for alley cat.
- Fixed mismatch IDs for two gacha coins.
0.2.0.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.2.0

0.2.0pre1.description:
Build that will eventually become the first stable release.

Changes:
- Split up settings.
  - This adds Shopsanity, Stat Shuffle, Quest for Sex.
  - Shopsanity adds all shops to be shuffled; otherwise they are vanilla.
  - Stat Shuffle shuffles the heart and mana containers.
  - Gachapon changed to Gachapon Shuffle and changed from a boolean to off, coins, gachapon.
  - Quest for Sex shuffles quests, from just Sensei's rewards up to sex experience itself.
- Adds location groups (though mostly for use with the new hinting system; still somewhat useful).
- Reordered items and locations, so the IDs are different.  Sorry Lazy!
- Adds a new hinting system.
  - Most NPCs that usually give you an item will tell you where the original item is vaguely.
  - Hint system looks for location group, then region, then if there's nothing usable says its "somewhere" in the person's game.
0.2.0pre1.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.2.0pre1

0.3.0-pre1.description:
New Features:
- Custom sprite support.  
  - You can import the graphics from KaitoKid's ArchipelagoUtilities or Stardew Valley's Custom Assets.  
  - Comes with generic Archipelago sprites and Lunacid sprites in 32x.
  - Supports custom descriptions.  Write some if you want,  Lunacid is used as an example.


Currently this still runs the 0.2.11 version.  There's no other changes.  Actual changes coming but I wanted people to experience this first at least.
0.3.0-pre1.title: Flipwitch Randomizer 0.3.0-pre1

1.0.0.description:
Screw 0.3.0 or whatever the number system is dumb anyway.

# New Features
- Starting Area Rando
  - You start one of the many crystal teleport spots in the game.  Some are excluded due to either triviality, or having zero sphere 1 checks.
- Shuffle Double Jump
  - You cannot double jump.  Logic for a double jump requires either the new item, or Angel Feathers.
- Shuffle Dodge
  - You cannot dodge.  Logic for dodging requires the item.  Ghost form gets to dodge to get through vines.
- Pottery Lottery
  - yay the location spam setting is here /monotone.  More seriously, pots drop items.  Do you remember them all?  Did I?
- Crystal Teleports
  - Checking a teleport panel gives you an item.  The ability to warp to one is an item.
- Universal Tracker
  - UT should work right now.  There's no poptracker support for it atm.
  - I literally just wrote this so there could be bugs.
- New Items!
  - Rose Ribbon: Allows you to double jump.
  - Orb of Avoidance: Allows you to dodge.

# Changes
- Massive logic overhaul, due to the above causing it.
- Updated whatever sprites Kaito has put together to something more recent.
1.0.0.title: Flipwitch Randomizer v1.0.0

1.0.0-pre1r7.description:
Screw 0.3.0 or whatever the number system is dumb anyway.

I'll likely put this as a release soon.

# Beta
This is a beta.  Not every feature I want (mainly internal settings) is in.  Logic might be bad or wrong.  The game itself might have bugs.  I'm releasing this as its "playable enough" IMO for more specific test case situations to come up.

# New Features
- Starting Area Rando
  - You start one of the many crystal teleport spots in the game.  Some are excluded due to either triviality, or having zero sphere 1 checks.
- Shuffle Double Jump
  - You cannot double jump.  Logic for a double jump requires either the new item, or Angel Feathers.
- Shuffle Dodge
  - You cannot dodge.  Logic for dodging requires the item.  Ghost form gets to dodge to get through vines.
- Pottery Lottery
  - yay the location spam setting is here /monotone.  More seriously, pots drop items.  Do you remember them all?  Did I?
- Crystal Teleports
  - Checking a teleport panel gives you an item.  The ability to warp to one is an item.
- Universal Tracker
  - UT should work right now.  There's no poptracker support for it atm.
  - I literally just wrote this so there could be bugs.
- New Items!
  - Rose Ribbon: Allows you to double jump.
  - Orb of Avoidance: Allows you to dodge.

# Changes
- Massive logic overhaul, due to the above causing it.
- Updated whatever sprites Kaito has put together to something more recent.

# Bugfixes on this while I've been away (idk not very exhaustive)
- Fixed some logic problems with Behind the Vines and Dirty Debut
- Added Demon Wings as a means of "Ghost Dodging" (You need to be able to dodge as ghost to slip past vines, and it counts).
- Add Abandoned Apartment to the list of zones for sewers.
1.0.0-pre1r7.title: [BETA] Flipwitch Randomizer v1.0.0
